<h2><a class="listing" style="link" href="/en/Dossiers/CTA-and-S-T/Selected-publications/Climate-frontline-African-communities-adapting-to-survive" title="Climate frontline: African communities adapting to survive " alt="link">Climate frontline: African communities adapting to survive </a></h2>

	
					<p>By Concern Universal, FARM-Africa, Find Your Feet, Self Help Africa and Utviklingsfondet/The Development Fund, 2009. Millions of farmers across Africa are already living with, and attempting to adapt to, the effects of climate change. But rarely are their voices heard. In Climate frontline, African men and women describe, in their own words, the strategies they have implemented in order to adapt and cope with their changing climate. </p>
							<p><span class="date">4/02/2010</span></p>
	<div class="cnt">
	<a class="link" href="/en/Dossiers/CTA-and-S-T/Selected-publications/Climate-frontline-African-communities-adapting-to-survive">Read more...</a>
